.TH UCC-CLI 1 "February 2026" "ucc-cli 0.1.1" "Uniwill Control Center"
.SH NAME
ucc-cli \- command-line interface for Uniwill Control Center
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ucc-cli
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ucc-cli
is a command-line client for the Uniwill Control Center daemon
.RB ( uccd ).
It communicates over D-Bus to query and control CPU/GPU performance profiles,
fan curves, keyboard backlighting, display brightness, webcam, Fn Lock,
water cooler hardware, and battery charging settings on Uniwill laptops.
.PP
The daemon must be running for any command to succeed.
Check with
.BR "systemctl status uccd" .
.SH COMMANDS
.SS General
.TP
.B status
Print a full system dashboard: active profile, CPU/GPU temperatures,
frequencies, power draw, fan speeds, hardware toggles, water cooler state,
and charging information.
Use
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output.
.TP
.B monitor \fR[\fB\-n\fR \fICOUNT\fR] [\fB\-i\fR \fISECS\fR]
Continuously print a compact one-line summary of CPU and GPU metrics
(temperature, frequency, power, fan speed).
Defaults to running indefinitely at 2-second intervals.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-n " COUNT"
Stop after
.I COUNT
samples (0 = infinite).
.TP
.BI \-i " SECS"
Polling interval in seconds (default: 2).
.RE
.SS Profile Management
.TP
.B profile list
List all built-in and custom profiles with their UUIDs and names.
.TP
.B profile get
Print the active profile as indented JSON.
.TP
.B profile set \fIPROFILE_ID\fR
Activate the profile identified by
.IR PROFILE_ID .
.TP
.B profile defaults
Print the built-in profiles as JSON.
.TP
.B profile customs
Print the custom profiles as JSON.
.TP
.B profile apply \fIJSON\fR
Apply a complete profile from a JSON string.
.TP
.B profile save \fIJSON\fR
Save a custom profile (creates or updates).
.TP
.B profile delete \fIPROFILE_ID\fR
Delete a custom profile.
.SS State Map
The state map controls automatic profile switching when the power source
changes (AC, battery, or water cooler).
.TP
.B statemap get
Print the current settings / state map as JSON.
.TP
.B statemap set \fISTATE\fR \fIPROFILE_ID\fR
Assign a profile to a power state.
Valid states:
.BR power_ac ,
.BR power_bat ,
.BR power_wc .
.SS Fan Control
.TP
.B fan list
List available fan profiles (built-in and custom) with their UUIDs.
.TP
.B fan get \fIFAN_PROFILE_ID\fR
Print the fan profile's curve data as JSON (keys:
.BR tableCPU ,
.BR tableGPU ,
.BR tablePump ,
.BR tableWaterCoolerFan ).
.TP
.B fan set \fIFAN_PROFILE_ID\fR
Activate a fan profile by its UUID.
The profile's curve keys are remapped and applied to the daemon.
Works with both built-in and custom fan profiles.
.TP
.B fan apply \fIJSON\fR
Apply fan curves directly.
The JSON must contain keys:
.BR cpu ,
.BR gpu ,
.BR pump ,
.BR waterCoolerFan
(each an array of temperature\[->]duty-percent points).
.TP
.B fan revert
Revert fan curves to the profile stored in the daemon.
.SS Keyboard Backlight
.TP
.B keyboard info
Print keyboard backlight capabilities (zone count, max brightness, max RGB values).
.TP
.B keyboard get
Print the current per-zone backlight state as a JSON array.
.TP
.B keyboard set \fIJSON\fR
Set per-zone backlight states from a JSON array.
Each element:
.nf
  { "mode": 0, "brightness": N, "red": R, "green": G, "blue": B }
.fi
.TP
.B keyboard color \fIR\fR \fIG\fR \fIB\fR [\fIBRIGHTNESS\fR]
Set a uniform colour across all keyboard zones.
.IR R ,
.IR G ,
.I B
are 0\-255.
.I BRIGHTNESS
defaults to 128.
.TP
.B keyboard profiles
List custom keyboard profiles (from local settings) with their UUIDs and names.
.TP
.B keyboard activate \fIPROFILE_ID\fR
Activate a custom keyboard profile by its UUID.
The profile's backlight data is sent to the daemon.
.SS Hardware Controls
.TP
.B brightness get
Print the current display brightness (0\-100).
.TP
.B brightness set \fIVALUE\fR
Set display brightness (0\-100).
.TP
.B webcam get
Print webcam status (\fBenabled\fR or \fBdisabled\fR).
.TP
.B webcam set \fIon\fR|\fIoff\fR
Enable or disable the webcam.
.TP
.B fnlock get
Print Fn Lock status (\fBon\fR or \fBoff\fR).
.TP
.B fnlock set \fIon\fR|\fIoff\fR
Enable or disable Fn Lock.
.SS Water Cooler
These commands control the Uniwill LCT water cooling system (if supported).
.TP
.B watercooler status
Print water cooler state: supported, enabled, fan speed and pump level
(only shown when the cooler is enabled and connected).
.TP
.B watercooler enable
Enable the water cooler (starts BLE scanning).
.TP
.B watercooler disable
Disable the water cooler.
.TP
.B watercooler fan \fIPERCENT\fR
Set the water cooler fan duty cycle (0\-100%).
.TP
.B watercooler pump \fICODE\fR
Set the pump voltage.
.IR CODE :
0 = 11 V, 1 = 12 V, 2 = 7 V, 3 = 8 V, 4 = off.
.TP
.B watercooler led \fIR\fR \fIG\fR \fIB\fR \fIMODE\fR
Set the water cooler LED colour and mode.
.IR R ,
.IR G ,
.I B
are 0\-255.
.IR MODE :
0 = static, 1 = breathe, 2 = colorful, 3 = breathe-color.
.TP
.B watercooler led-off
Turn off the water cooler LED.
.SS Charging
.TP
.B charging status
Print charging profile, priority, type, and charge thresholds.
Only shown if the hardware supports charging control.
.TP
.B charging set-profile \fIDESCRIPTOR\fR
Set the firmware-level charging profile.
.TP
.B charging set-priority \fIDESCRIPTOR\fR
Set the USB-C PD charging priority.
.TP
.B charging set-thresholds \fISTART\fR \fIEND\fR
Set the battery charge start and end thresholds (percent).
.SS System Information
.TP
.B cpu
Show CPU info: core count, temperature, frequency, power, available
governors and energy-performance preferences.
.TP
.B gpu
Show GPU info, NVIDIA power control details, and cTGP offset.
.TP
.B power-limits
Show ODM power limits.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output machine-readable JSON instead of human-readable text.
Currently applies to the
.B status
command.
.TP
.BR \-\-help ", " \-h
Print usage information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-version ", " \-v
Print version and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Command error (bad arguments, D-Bus method failure).
.TP
.B 2
Cannot connect to the uccd daemon.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B ucc-cli
communicates with the
.B com.uniwill.uccd
D-Bus service on the system bus.
The daemon is typically managed via systemd:
.PP
.RS
.nf
systemctl start uccd
systemctl enable uccd
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/uccrc
Local user configuration (custom profiles, fan profiles, keyboard profiles,
state map).
Shared with
.B ucc-gui
and
.BR ucc-tray .
.SH EXAMPLES
Show a live monitoring dashboard:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli status
.fi
.RE
.PP
Monitor CPU/GPU every 1 second, 10 samples:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli monitor -i 1 -n 10
.fi
.RE
.PP
List and activate a profile:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli profile list
ucc-cli profile set 01234567-abcd-ef01-2345-6789abcdef01
.fi
.RE
.PP
Set keyboard to solid red at full brightness:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli keyboard color 255 0 0 255
.fi
.RE
.PP
Get full status as JSON (for scripting):
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli status --json | jq .cpu.temperature
.fi
.RE
.PP
Set charge thresholds to start at 40% and stop at 80%:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli charging set-thresholds 40 80
.fi
.RE
.PP
Control water cooler LED (green, breathe mode):
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli watercooler led 0 255 0 1
.fi
.RE
.PP
Activate a fan profile:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli fan list
ucc-cli fan set 01234567-abcd-ef01-2345-6789abcdef01
.fi
.RE
.PP
List and activate a keyboard profile:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ucc-cli keyboard profiles
ucc-cli keyboard activate 01234567-abcd-ef01-2345-6789abcdef01
.fi
.RE
